ort.</li><li>100% of donations for missions go to <strong>MISSIONS</strong>!</li><li>Every project considered for missions resources are <strong>VETTED</strong> through our missions team made up of your peers and church board.</li><li>Our focus is on <strong>REACHING</strong> the <strong>UNREACHED</strong> people groups of the world with the love of Christ.</li><li>We invest in projects that are <strong>SUSTAINABLE</strong> and <strong>REPRODUCIBLE.</strong></li></ul><h3>Missions Convention Schedule</h3><h4>Sunday, January 20th at 9:00 AM &amp; 10:45 AM</h4><p><strong>Adult Services:</strong>&nbsp;A presentation by guest speaker Dr. Howard Foltz will focus on the beauty of spiritual transformation and on the value and importance of a strategic investment in missions through a &ldquo;Faith Promise.&rdquo; What is a &ldquo;Faith Promise?&rdquo;&nbsp; Your invited to come and find out.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Children Services:</strong>&nbsp;A presentation by missionaries to children in Africa, letting every child hear and experience stories about children whose lives have been changed by Christ, just like children in America.&nbsp;</p><p><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=1887313&amp;fileName=graphic--photo--howard-foltz-0-0-151-183.jpg" width="151" height="183" alt="GRAPHIC : PHOTO : Howard Foltz" title="GRAPHIC : PHOTO : Howard Foltz" style="vertical-align: text-bottom;"></p><h5><strong>Howard Foltz</strong><br><span class="title">President of AIMS - Accelerating International Mission Strategies</span></h5><p>Dr. Howard Foltz, established AIMS (Accelerating International Mission Strategies) in 1991. Since that time he and a team of trainers leaders have equipped over 100,000 indigenous pastors around the world. As a result of the training an estimated 30.1 million peole have heard the Gospel, most for the first time. Over 28,000 churches have been planted among unreached people groups by these partners of AIM. Dr. Foltz&rsquo;s leadership focus is to work with churches such as Portland Christian Center to maximize the efforts of everyone involved.</p><h4>Sunday, January 20th at 6:00 PM</h4><p><strong>Evening Dessert and Adult Teaching:</strong> Dr. Howard Foltz will present stories of transformation within the muslim communities in our own country and prepare us to be effective ambassadors in our own neighborhoods.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Children Night:</strong> Special Children&rsquo;s activities will provide our kids with a night of learning, fun, and interaction with missions and missionaries.&nbsp;</p><h4>Tuesday, January 22nd at 9:30 AM</h4><p><strong>Ladies Bible Study:</strong> One of our "unnamed" missionaries from the Middle East will be our special guest for this "ladies only" session. We can't say any more in print, but ladies, you will want to make time for this presentation.&nbsp;</p><h4>Wednesday, January 23rd at 7:00 PM</h4><p><strong>Youth Missions Night:&nbsp;</strong> Pastor&rsquo;s Caleb Bryant and Aaron McKee, our High School and Middle School leaders will present to our youth the awesome missions experiences and the results they have seen first hand on the field. Our students will find out the many ways they can be involved in missions, now and in the future.&nbsp;</p><h4>Friday, January 25th at 7:00 PM</h4><p><strong>A2:</strong> Our Young Adults group will continue their missions journey under the leadership of Pastor Caleb and Jonette Bryant. Over a year ago, members of this group traveled to Brazil and the results were astounding. This night they will focus on the next steps.&nbsp;</p><h4>Friday, January 25th at 9:00 PM</h4><p><strong>High School Underground Church:&nbsp;</strong>Students will gather at the church for this overnight event and read through the New Testament in conditions much like people around the world who cannot openly worship and study the Word (candlelight only, no chairs, and food you might find in third world countries). The night will conclude with worship and prayer for our world.&nbsp;</p><h4>Sunday, January 27th at 9:00 AM &amp; 10:45 AM</h4><p><strong>Adult Services:</strong> This special service brings to a close the 2013 Missions Convention with an opportunity for every person of every age to make a &ldquo;Faith Promise&rdquo; for missions. Pastor Ray will also introduce a special couple from our own congregation who recently have become appointed missionaires. It&rsquo;s the beginning of a new outreach for PCC. You won&rsquo;t want to miss this morning service!&nbsp;<br><br><strong>Children Services:</strong> Pastor Phil Hahn has a wonderful morning planned for all of our children. Make certain that your child or grandchild doesn&rsquo;t miss this Special Missions Sunday at PCC.</p><h3>Would you like to learn more about how to get involved with local and global missions? &nbsp;</h3><p><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/outreach/" class="button"><span>Outreach Information</span>&nbsp;</a></p></div>